**I've tried Xamarin Forms all the way up to Version 3.1.0.469394-pre1 with the same results.
Android and iOS ads work perfect. UWP ads work fine on startup. They work fine when I navigate to another page. But when I use**

`await Navigation.PopModalAsync();`

**with UWP, I get an exception in this method:**
```
 protected override void OnElementChanged(ElementChangedEventArgs<AdControlView> e)
        {
            base.OnElementChanged(e);

            //if (e.NewElement == null)
            //    return;

            try
            {
                if (Control == null)
                {
                    CreateNativeAdControl();
                    SetNativeControl(adView);
                }
            }
            catch (Exception ex)
            {
                Console.WriteLine(ex);
                return;
            }
        }
```
**This is the exception:**

`System.InvalidOperationException: 'Cannot assign a native control without an Element; Renderer unbound and/or disposed. Please consult Xamarin.Forms renderers for reference implementation of OnElementChanged.'`


**If I include this, then the app doesn't crash, but I no longer have an ad on the page:**

```
if (e.NewElement == null)
                return;
```

